"{\"uid\": \"qz.com.-720114-brexit-wont-help-the-uk-lure-tech-giants-away-from-ireland-with-sweetheart-tax-deals-\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"With the widespread perception that Apple enjoys a tiny tax bill in the United Kingdom, even as it earns hundreds of millions from consumers here, the tech giant usually sees some public scrutiny when it files its accounts.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.643069898494891e-13, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 72, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7785349033016846, \"rank\": 0.2844635764119866, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the widespread perception\", \"from\": 5, \"to\": 30}, {\"ngram\": \"a tiny tax bill\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 64}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds of millions\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125}, {\"ngram\": \"consumers\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 140}, {\"ngram\": \"the tech giant\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 161}, {\"ngram\": \"some public scrutiny\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 195}, {\"ngram\": \"its accounts\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when Apple filed for its UK businesses on June 23, the shock of the Brexit result ensured that there was plenty of other news to keep everyone occupied.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Apple\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 239}, {\"ngram\": \"its UK businesses\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 267}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 275}, {\"ngram\": \"the shock\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brexit result\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"other news\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 354}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Apple's filings did not go completely unnoticed, the public could not muster its annual outpouring of outrage around the company's perceived manipulation of its tax bill.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Apple's filings\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"its annual outpouring\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"outrage\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"the company's perceived manipulation\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 541}, {\"ngram\": \"its tax bill\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Apple reported that it paid \\u00a312.9 million ($17 million) in UK corporation tax for 2015, on the back of pre-tax profit of \\u00a3106 million for its two main UK entities, Apple Retail UK Ltd and Apple (UK) Ltd. That was derived from revenues of over \\u00a31 billion from those two companies.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advertisement Apple\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"UK corporation tax\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"pre-tax profit\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 691}, {\"ngram\": \"its two main UK entities\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"Apple Retail UK Ltd\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"Apple (UK\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"Ltd.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"revenues\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"those two companies\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the seemingly paltry amounts of tax paid compared to the vast sums in sales that raises eyebrows.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the seemingly paltry amounts\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"tax\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"the vast sums\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"sales\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"eyebrows\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apple, of course, is having its tax affairs investigated by the European commission.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Apple\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 964}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"its tax affairs\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"the European commission\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1042}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's because its European holding company is located in Dublin, which has a much lower corporation tax rate of 12.5%, compared to the UK's 20%, and that's where the bulk of its profits flow.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its European holding company\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"Dublin\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"a much lower corporation tax rate\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1153}, {\"ngram\": \"12.5%\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"the UK's 20%\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"the bulk\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"its profits\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the UK leaves the EU, that means Apple's UK companies would no longer fall under European commission jurisdiction-or investigation.\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the UK\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"the EU\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"Apple's UK companies\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"European commission jurisdiction\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"investigation\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One theory goes that the UK could then become an attractive location for Apple's European holding company, allowing the company to shift profits out of the EU and into newly independent Britain.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One theory\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"the UK\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"an attractive location\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1441}, {\"ngram\": \"Apple's European holding company\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1500}, {\"ngram\": \"profits\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"the EU\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"newly independent Britain\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UK's tax authorities, after all, have already shown that they are willing to cut deals with tech giants, like Google, who have been remiss on their payments.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The UK's tax authorities\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"deals\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"tech giants\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"Google\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"their payments\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That might seem preferable to staying in the EU, and continuing to run the risk of probes from individual member states, as Google was subjected to in Paris recently.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the EU\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"probes\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1819}, {\"ngram\": \"individual member states\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"Google\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea of the UK supplanting Ireland as base for global tech companies is not entirely alien.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"the UK supplanting Ireland\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"base\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"global tech companies\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rohan Silva, a former adviser to David Cameron on tech policy matters, has called for post-Brexit UK to slash its corporation tax rate in half, to 10%, the world's lowest, precisely to attract relocating companies.\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rohan Silva\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"a former adviser\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"David Cameron\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2040}, {\"ngram\": \"tech policy matters\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"post-Brexit UK\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2094}, {\"ngram\": \"its corporation tax rate\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"10%\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"relocating companies\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement But the reality is that a post-Brexit UK would make little sense as a European holding company.\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advertisement\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"a post-Brexit UK\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"little sense\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"a European holding company\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the UK leaves the bloc, dividends, interest payments, and royalties remitted from a subsidiary in an EU member state can no longer benefit from a withholding tax exemption provided by the EU.\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the UK\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"the bloc\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2348}, {\"ngram\": \"dividends\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"interest payments\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"royalties\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"a subsidiary\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2420}, {\"ngram\": \"an EU member state\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"a withholding tax exemption\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"the EU\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That exemption is currently offered under an EU directive that allows these payments to be made between a parent company and a subsidiary, or vice versa, located in EU member states.\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That exemption\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2532}, {\"ngram\": \"an EU directive\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"these payments\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2602}, {\"ngram\": \"a parent company\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"a subsidiary\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2655}, {\"ngram\": \"EU member states\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the exemption is removed, it translates into an estimated additional 5-15% of withholding tax on interest, royalty, or dividend payments, depending on the country, if a company were to repatriate its profits to the UK, says Markus Meiner, a director at the advocacy and research group, the Tax Justice Network.\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 3017, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the exemption\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"an estimated additional 5-15%\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2781}, {\"ngram\": \"withholding tax\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2812}, {\"ngram\": \"royalty\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2821}, {\"ngram\": \"dividend payments\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2843}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2858, \"to\": 2869}, {\"ngram\": \"a company\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2883}, {\"ngram\": \"its profits\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2914}, {\"ngram\": \"the UK\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 2924}, {\"ngram\": \"Markus Meiner\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2944}, {\"ngram\": \"a director\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 2956}, {\"ngram\": \"the advocacy and research group\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tax Justice Network\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even reduced UK tax rates would be outweighed by taxes levied on subsidiaries in EU member states.\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even reduced UK tax rates\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3043}, {\"ngram\": \"taxes\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"subsidiaries\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3095}, {\"ngram\": \"EU member states\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It would make the UK the worst place as a holding location, no matter what sweetheart deals are offered by the UK,\\\" Meinzer says.\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the UK\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3138}, {\"ngram\": \"a holding location\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"sweetheart deals\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"the UK\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3231}, {\"ngram\": \"Meinzer\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are other factors that diminish the UK's attractiveness as a new European base for big tech firms.\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3353, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other factors\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3272}, {\"ngram\": \"the UK's attractiveness\", \"from\": 3287, \"to\": 3310}, {\"ngram\": \"a new Europ